### Precision in Scientific Research and the redefinition of the kg

Nonlinear lasers are indispensable tools in scientific research. 
They enable ultrafast spectroscopy and microscopy techniques, providing insights into the dynamic
 processes occurring on femtosecond (10^-15 seconds) timescales. For example, femtosecond lasers,
  which operate in the nonlinear regime, are used to study chemical reactions and biological processes at an 
  atomic and molecular level. This precision helps scientists to understand fundamental phenomena and develop new materials and technologies.



